s with&nbsp;Belgium,&nbsp;Luxembourg,&nbsp;Germany,&nbsp;Switzerland,&nbsp;Monaco,&nbsp;Italy,&nbsp;Andorra,&nbsp;Spain, and the Netherlands. It&nbsp;spans a combined area of 643,801&nbsp;km2&nbsp;(248,573&nbsp;sq&nbsp;mi) and over 67 million people (as of May&nbsp;2021). Its capital is&nbsp;Paris, the country&#39;s&nbsp;largest city&nbsp;and main cultural and commercial center.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#202122\">France is a&nbsp;developed country&nbsp;with the world&#39;s&nbsp;seventh-largest economy. France retains its centuries-long status as a global center of&nbsp;art,&nbsp;science, and&nbsp;philosophy. It is the world&#39;s leading tourist destination, receiving over 89&nbsp;million foreign&nbsp;visitors&nbsp;in 2018.&nbsp;France is one of the five&nbsp;permanent members of the United Nations Security Council. France is a founding and&nbsp;leading&nbsp;member of the European Union&nbsp;and the&nbsp;Eurozone, as well as a key member of the&nbsp;North Atlantic Treaty Organization&nbsp;(NATO).</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#548dd4\">Tourist&nbsp; Visa&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Work&nbsp; Visa &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Business Visa&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:22.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#548dd4\">Tourist&n